                <div2 type="section" subtype="handwritten">
                <p>To the Commissioners appointed under the act of Congress of <date when="1862-04-16">April 16, 1862</date>, entitled, "An Act for the release
                    of certain persons held to service or labor in the <placeName>District of
                        Columbia</placeName>."</p>
                <p>The Petition of <persName>Peter Von Essen</persName>, of <placeName>Georgetown
                        D.C.</placeName> respectfully shews, that he is a person loyal to the
                        <placeName>United States</placeName>, who, at the time of the passage of the
                    Act of Congress aforesaid, held a claim to service or labor against certain persons of
                    African descent, for and during their lives, who were discharged from such
                    claim, by said act, that he has caused said persons to be carefully valued by
                    disinterested persons and they are of the names, description and values
                    following, viz:</p>

